## This file is automatically generated from /etc/audit/rules.d
# task filter-list rule (f3 section 2.3; flagtab.h:25-29 AUDIT_FILTER_TASK 'task').
# The task list matches at TASK CREATION (fork/clone) time, evaluating only the
# inherited task attributes -- it cannot see syscall args. auditctl(8) notes the
# task list is DISABLED BY DEFAULT for the never-suppress case; an always,task rule
# fires once per process creation but carries very little, near-zero net volume here
# because we narrow it tightly. Valid, distinct list. LOW/near-zero tier.
-a always,task -F 'auid>=1000' -F 'auid!=unset' -k task_create
